Monsignor Fraser College (also called as Monsignor Fraser, MFC, or Fraser) is a Roman Catholic specialized dual-track Alternative and Adult High School run by the Toronto Catholic District School Board in Toronto, Ontario, Canada with six campuses and various programs. The school was named in honour of John Andrew Mary Fraser (1887-September 3, 1962), the founder of the Scarborough Foreign Mission Society and a missionary.[1]
